A KCSE exam candidate at Witharaga Mixed Secondary School (pictured) in Migori missed exams on Wednesday after reportedly being abducted.  Martine Odhiambo, a bright student from a poor background left home to go an revise but never returned. Police said they were investigating.  A classmate said she received a text from Odhiambo, saying he had been abducted by people in a Probox . He said it was heading towards Ogwedhi centre on the border with Narok. He gave no reason. “He left home about 8pm to go for revision. I thought he was at relative’s or neighbour’s house,” his mother said. 